EscapeVelocityFormula

The Escape Velocity Formula

The speed that an object must have in order to escape the gravitational pull of a spherical, non-rotating body is dependent on the mass of the body and the radius of the body.

v = \sqrt{\frac{2 G M}{R}}

where:

v [var. scal. EscapeSpeed, L T^{-1}, m s^{-1}] is the escape speed if the object moves radially away from the body
G [const. scal. UniversalGravitationalConstant] is the Universal Gravitational Constant
M [var. scal. Mass, M, kg] is the mass of the body
R [var. scal. Radius, L, m] is the radius of the body


